      <br>
      <p class="text-1"><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Potatoes, pulses, nuts:</span> Plastic and energetic function. Energetic in the sense that they provide energy thanks to their carbohydrate content. As for pulses, they provide proteins of vegetable origin with a high biological content and fibre. Nuts provide monounsaturated and polyunsaturated fatty acids and B vitamins.</p>
      <a class="a-2" href="/products/group3">Create Product</a>
      <br>
    </div>
    <foot class="foot-6">
      <h1 style="font-family: serif; font-size: 50px; color: rgba(158, 154, 97, 0.829);">Group 4</h1>
      <br>
      <p class="text-1"><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Vegetables:</span> Regulatory function. The Spanish Food Code indicates that vegetables are any herbaceous horticultural plant that can be used as food, either raw or cooked, and greens are vegetables in which the edible part is made up of their green organs (leaves, stems, inflorescence). They provide large amounts of vitamins, minerals and trace elements, fibre (especially soluble), as well as a high percentage of water and few calories from their low proportion of carbohydrates, proteins and fats.</p>
      <a class="a-2"  href="/products/group4">Create Product</a>
      <br>
    </foot>
  </div>
